The efferent vessels of the  ascend upon the trachea and unite with efferents of the internal mammary and anterior mediastinal glands to form the right and left '''bronchomediastinal trunks'''. 
The right bronchomediastinal trunk may join the , and the left the , but more frequently they open independently of these ducts into the junction of the  and s of their own side.